|-\n| colspan=\"22\" style=\"font-size:85%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a single that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n===As featured artist===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:21em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Laidback Luke|1234]]\"<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">([[Laidback Luke]] featuring [[Chuckie (DJ)|Chuckie]] and Martin Solveig)</span>\n| 2012\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.martinsolveig.com}}\n\n{{Martin Solveig}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martin Solveig discography}}\n[[Category:Discographies of French artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = [[Martin Solveig]]\n| Logo         =\n| Image        = Martin_Solveig_Pukkelpop_2009.jpg\n| Caption      = Solveig at [[Pukkelpop]] music festival\n| Studio       = 5\n| Compilation  = 1\n| Live         =\n| Video        =\n| Music videos =\n| Singles      = 26\n}}\n\nThe discography of [[Martin Solveig]], a French DJ and record producer, consists of four [[studio album]]s, one [[compilation album]] and twenty-six [[Single (music)|singles]] (including one as a featured artist).\n\nHis debut studio album, ''Sur la terre'', was released in June 2002. The album includes the singles \"[[Madan (song)|Madan]]\", \"[[Rocking Music]]\" and \"[[I'm a Good Man]]\".\n\nHis second studio album, ''Hedonist'', was released in September 2005, the album peaked at number 43 on the [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|French Albums Chart]]. The album includes the singles \"[[Everybody (Martin Solveig song)|Everybody]]\", \"[[Jealousy (Martin Solveig song)|Jealousy]]\", \"Something Better\" and \"[[Rejection (song)|Rejection]]\".\n\nHis third studio album, ''[[C'est la Vie (Martin Solveig album)|C'est la Vie]]'', was released in October 2008, the album peaked at number 16 on the [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|French Albums Chart]].  \"[[C'est la Vie (Martin Solveig song)|C'est la Vie]]\" was released as the lead single from the album on 21 January 2008. \"[[I Want You (Martin Solveig song)|I Want You]]\" was released as the second single from the album on 15 September 2008. \"[[One 2.3 Four]]\" was released as the third single from the album on 22 December 2008. \"[[Boys & Girls (Martin Solveig song)|Boys & Girls]]\" was released as the fourth single from the album on 28 September 2009.\n\nHis fourth studio album, ''[[Smash (Martin Solveig album)|Smash]]'', was released in June 2011, peaking at number 18 on the [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|French Albums Chart]]. On 6 September 2010 he released the single \"[[Hello (Martin Solveig song)|Hello]]\" with [[Dragonette]] as the lead single from the album. It is Solveig's most successful single to date, peaking at number one in [[Austria]], [[Belgium]] ([[Flanders]]), [[Czech Republic]] and the [[Netherlands]], while charting within the top 10 in ten other countries. The song also peaked at number 13 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. \"[[Ready 2 Go]]\" was released as the second single from the album on 28 March 2011. On 24 October 2011 \"[[Big in Japan (Martin Solveig song)|Big in Japan]]\" was released as the third single from the album. On 2 April 2012 \"[[The Night Out]]\" was released as the fourth single from the album.\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11.5em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18.5em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"6\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Martin+Solveig|title=Discographie Martin Solveig|publisher=French Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Martin+Solveig|title=Discografie Martin Solveig|publisher=Belgium (Flanders) Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (Wa)]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br/><ref name=\"GER\">{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/|title=Discographie Martin Solveig|format=enter \"Martin Solveig\" into the \"Suchen\" box|publisher=German Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br/><ref name=\"SWI\">{{cite web|url=http://hitparade.ch/artist/Martin_Solveig|title=Discographie Martin Solveig|publisher=Swiss Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[US Dance/Electronic Albums|US Dance]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Sur la Terre]]''\n|\n* Released: 17 June 2002\n* Label: Penso Positivo\n* Format: [[Music download|Digital download]], [[Compact disc|CD]]\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Suite''{{Ref label|note_a1|A}}\n|\n* Released: 24 June 2003\n* Label: Penso Positivo\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 84 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Hedonist (album)|Hedonist]]''\n|\n* Released: 12 September 2005\n* Label: Penso Positivo\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 43 || 99 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[C'est la Vie (Martin Solveig album)|C'est la Vie]]''\n|\n* Released: 28 October 2008\n* Label: Temps D'Avance\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 16 || 99 || 23 || \u2014 || 59 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Smash (Martin Solveig album)|Smash]]''\n|\n* Released: 6 June 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/smash/id439636826 |title=iTunes \u2013 Musique \u2013 Smash par Martin Solveig |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |accessdate=2012-03-23}}</ref>\n* Label: [[Mercury Records]]\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 18 || \u2014 || 37 || 84 || 77 || 22\n|-\n| colspan=\"22\" style=\"font-size:85%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes an album that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Compilation albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11.5em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18.5em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br/><ref name=\"SWI\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[So Far (Martin Solveig album)|So Far]]''\n|\n* Released: 2006\n* Label: Interowners\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 38 || 100 || 85\n|}\n\n==Singles==\n===As lead artist===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:21em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br/><ref name=\"AUS\">Peak positions in Australi